.TH VEXT-SEND 1 "December 2025" "vext 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
vext-send \- send notifications to vextd daemon
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B vext-send
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fIMESSAGE\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B vext-send
is a command-line utility to send notifications to a running vextd daemon.
It formats and sends JSON notifications via UDP.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-server =\fIADDRESS\fR
vextd server address (default: 127.0.0.1:6659)
.TP
.BR \-t ", " \-\-to =\fITARGET\fR
IRC target URL (can be specified multiple times)
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-project =\fINAME\fR
Project name
.TP
.BR \-b ", " \-\-branch =\fINAME\fR
Branch name
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-commit =\fIHASH\fR
Commit hash
.TP
.BR \-a ", " \-\-author =\fINAME\fR
Author name
.TP
.BR \-u ", " \-\-url =\fIURL\fR
URL to include
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print help message and exit
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Print version information and exit
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B VEXT_SERVER
Default vextd server address
.TP
.B VEXT_TARGETS
Comma-separated default IRC targets
.TP
.B VEXT_PROJECT
Default project name
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Send a simple message:
.RS
.nf
vext-send -t irc://irc.libera.chat/#vext "Hello, world!"
.fi
.RE
.PP
Send a commit notification:
.RS
.nf
vext-send -t irc://irc.libera.chat/#vext \\
  -p myproject -b main -c abc1234 \\
  -a "John Doe" "Fixed bug in parser"
.fi
.RE
.PP
Send to multiple channels:
.RS
.nf
vext-send -t irc://irc.libera.chat/#dev \\
  -t irc://irc.libera.chat/#commits \\
  "New release v1.0.0"
.fi
.RE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
Failed to send notification
.TP
.B 2
Invalid arguments
